#. <section class="sutta" id="sn46.8"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn46.8:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 46"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 46"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn46.8:0.2"
msgid "1. Pabbatavagga"
msgstr "1. Mountains"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn46.8:0.3"
msgid "8. Upavānasutta"
msgstr "8. With Upavāna"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.8:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā ca upavāno āyasmā ca sāriputto kosambiyaṃ viharanti "
"ghositārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the venerables Upavāna and Sāriputta were staying near Kosambi, "
"in Ghosita’s Monastery."

msgctxt "sn46.8:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yenāyasmā "
"upavāno tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā upavānena saddhiṃ sammodi."
msgstr ""
"Then in the late afternoon, Venerable Sāriputta came out of retreat, went to "
"Venerable Upavāna and exchanged greetings with him."

msgctxt "sn46.8:1.3"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantaṃ upavānaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one "
"side and said to Upavāna:"

# paccattaṃ yonisomanasikārā occurs at SN 46.8, MN 50, and DN 28. In MN 50 it clearly means “investigate inside himself”. The same meaning makes sense in SN 46.8. In DN 28, it is applied to another.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.8:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Jāneyya nu kho, āvuso upavāna, bhikkhu ‘paccattaṃ yonisomanasikārā evaṃ "
"susamāraddhā me satta bojjhaṅgā phāsuvihārāya saṃvattantī’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Reverend Upavāna, can a mendicant know by investigating inside themselves "
"that the seven awakening factors are well implemented so that they lead to "
"living at ease?”"

# quotes incorrect
msgctxt "sn46.8:2.2"
msgid ""
"“Jāneyya kho, āvuso sāriputta, bhikkhu ‘paccattaṃ yonisomanasikārā evaṃ "
"susamāraddhā me satta bojjhaṅgā phāsuvihārāya saṃvattantī’”ti."
msgstr "“They can, Reverend Sāriputta."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.77"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.8:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Satisambojjhaṅgaṃ kho, āvuso, bhikkhu ārabbhamāno pajānāti ‘cittañca me "
"suvimuttaṃ, thinamiddhañca me susamūhataṃ, uddhaccakukkuccañca me "
"suppaṭivinītaṃ, āraddhañca me vīriyaṃ, aṭṭhiṃ katvā manasi karomi, no ca "
"līnan’ti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"As a mendicant rouses up the awakening factor of mindfulness, they "
"understand: ‘My mind is well freed. I’ve eradicated dullness and drowsiness, "
"and eliminated restlessness and remorse. My energy is roused up, and my mind "
"is sharply focused, not sluggish.’ …"

msgctxt "sn46.8:3.2"
msgid ""
"upekkhāsambojjhaṅgaṃ āvuso, bhikkhu ārabbhamāno pajānāti ‘cittañca me "
"suvimuttaṃ, thinamiddhañca me susamūhataṃ, uddhaccakukkuccañca me "
"suppaṭivinītaṃ, āraddhañca me vīriyaṃ, aṭṭhiṃ katvā manasi karomi, no ca "
"līnan’”ti."
msgstr ""
"As they rouse up the awakening factor of equanimity, they understand: ‘My "
"mind is well freed. I’ve eradicated dullness and drowsiness, and eliminated "
"restlessness and remorse. My energy is roused up, and my mind is sharply "
"focused, not sluggish.’"

msgctxt "sn46.8:3.3"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ kho, āvuso sāriputta, bhikkhu jāneyya ‘paccattaṃ yonisomanasikārā evaṃ "
"susamāraddhā me satta bojjhaṅgā phāsuvihārāya saṃvattantī’”ti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant can know by investigating inside themselves that the "
"seven awakening factors are well implemented so that they lead to living at "
"ease.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn46.8:3.4"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
